The paper proposes a system based on matrix factorization and deep recurrent neural networks for genotype imputation and phenotype sequences prediction. The paper deals with analyzing modern biological data, which is a common topic in the field of bioinformatics and computational biology. The use of deep learning techniques such as deep recurrent neural networks and matrix factorization suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also deals with analyzing genetic data, which may suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) as genetic data is often visualized and analyzed using image processing techniques. Finally, the paper deals with predicting phenotypic sequences, which may suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of computational biology (cs.BIO).
